# This directory is mounted into Grafana and scanned by the file-based
# dashboard provisioner (see ../provisioning/dashboards/dashboards.yaml).
#
# It is intentionally empty. Drop a *.json dashboard model here to have it
# auto-provisioned on startup.
#
# The authorization-audit dashboard lives in ../dashboards-available/ instead
# of here on purpose: Grafana 10.2.3's file provisioner rejects it on every
# load with "could not resolve dashboards:uid:authorization-audit: Dashboard
# not found" (an upstream provisioner regression, see grafana/grafana#73043 and
# #87342 — not a problem with the dashboard JSON itself). Keeping it out of the
# provisioned path stops that error from spamming the logs. Import it manually
# instead — see ../dashboards-available/README.md.
